    <section class="container" id="tips">
        <h2 class="section-title">Resume Writing Tips</h2>
        <div style="background: white; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: var(--shadow); margin: 2rem 0;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--secondary-color);">1. Tailor Your Resume for Each Job</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Customize your resume for each position you apply for. Highlight the skills and experiences most relevant to the job description.</p>
            
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--secondary-color);">2. Use Action Verbs</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Start bullet points with strong action verbs like "developed," "managed," "increased," or "implemented" to demonstrate your impact.</p>
            
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--secondary-color);">3. Quantify Achievements</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Where possible, include numbers to quantify your accomplishments (e.g., "Increased sales by 20%" or "Managed a team of 5 developers").</p>
            
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--secondary-color);">4. Keep It Concise</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Aim for 1-2 pages maximum. Be selective about what you include and focus on recent, relevant experiences.</p>
            
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--secondary-color);">5. Proofread Carefully</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Typos and grammatical errors can get your resume rejected immediately. Proofread multiple times and consider having someone else review it.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    
